  <div class="information-title">About Artist Accounts</div>
  <p>On <b>Sublimation Kitchen</b> you are not just a creator. Everyone on <b>Sublimation Kitchen</b> platform has the opportunity build their own independent fashion brand, sell clothing and accessories created by them and earn money. Long story short, you create the graphics and we take care of all the rest including marketing, manufacturing and delivery. You get paid for every sold. Got your attention? Then read on.</p>

  <p class="question">What are Artist Accounts?</p>
  <p class="answer">Think of them as an extension for a regular Sublimation Kitchen Account. Every registered user can upgrade to an artist account through a simple verification. Whenever an item created by that user is sold, 20% of the revenue goes straight to them.</p>

  <p class="question">What is the difference between a artist profile and a regular profile?</p>
  <p class="answer">As mentioned above, the artist gets 20% revenue of every sold item created by them and published by their artist account. Also artists can have a banner visible at the top of the brand page, a logo and short bio.</p>

  <p class="question">What do I need to create a brand?</p>
  <p class="answer">
    In order to create your own brand on Sublimation Kitchen you’ll need:
    <ul>
      <li>A <b>Sublimation Kitchen</b> account</li>
      <li>A PayPal Account</li>
      <li>1$ to verify your identity</li>
    </ul>
    Although creating and registering an artist account is free, you still need to make a $1 payment through your PayPal so that we can verify your identity and link your PayPal and <b>Sublimation Kitchen</b> accounts together.
  </p>

  <p class="question">How can I create an artist account?</p>
  <p class="answer">
    Creating an account is as easy as 1,2,3, we will guide you through the process step by step.
    <ol>
      <li>Create a Sublimation Kitchen account.</li>
      <li>After creating the account go to the profile settings page, or click <a href="/profile">HERE</a>.</li>
      <li>Click Create Artist Account button.</li>
      <li>Next, fulfill the brand information, accept Sublimation Kitchen Terms & Conditions and verify your identity by transferring $1 via your PayPal account.</li>
      <li>You are done, click <a href="/profile/artist">HERE</a> to configure your brand.</li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p class="question">Where can I set my logo, banner and my artist description?</p>
  <p class="answer">You can set or change your brand banner, logo and description on your brand settings page or by clicking <a href="/profile/artist">HERE</a>.</p>

  <p class="question">How should my artist banner and logo be?</p>
  <p class="answer">Your artist collection banner should be at least 1240x435 pixels, your logo should be at least 400 x 400 pixels.</p>

  <p class="question">I sold an item. Now what?</p>
  <p class="answer">Basically nothing. We will manufacture the item and deliver it to the customer. You’ll get 20% commission of every transaction generated by your brand without even moving from your couch.</p>

  <p class="question">Will you promote my items?</p>
  <p class="answer">Sure, why not?! We constantly promote the whole platform and also standalone designers whose designs are attractive and popular.</p>

  <p class="question">How can I promote my brand myself?</p>
  <p class="answer">We will send you three discount codes worth 30% after 7, 30, 90 and 180 days of being our brand so you could get things going. You can give the codes to your friends, family, post them on social media, organize a contest or simply use them yourself to buy your own clothes. The codes are valid one month.</p>

  <p class="question">How do I get paid?</p>
  <p class="answer">After you collect at least $25 worth of artist earnings, you can request a money transfer to your PayPal account.</p>

  <p class="question">Where can I check how much I’ve earned?</p>
  <p class="answer">You can check it on your brand settings page or by clicking <a href="/profile/artist">HERE</a>.</p>

  <p class="question">Where do I find the Paypal Transfer option for my earnings?</p>
  <p class="answer">You can transfer your artist earnings to your PayPal account on your artist settings page or by clicking <a href="/profile/artist">HERE</a>. After you collect at least $25 an additional “Transfer money” button will appear next to your artist stats.</p>
